{"heading":"Saints must live righteously after baptism.","number":3,"verseCount":15,"verses":[[1,["Put them in mind to be ",["subject",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Citizenship","tg/citizenship"],"."]]]," to ",["principalities",["study-note-ref","b",[["TG Governments","tg/governments"],"."]]]," and powers, to obey magistrates, to be ready to every good work,"]],[2,["To ",["speak evil",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Slander","tg/slander"],"."]]]," of no man, to be ",["no brawlers",["study-note-ref","b",["GR not quarrelsome."]]],", ",["but",["clarity-word"]]," gentle, shewing all ",["meekness",["study-note-ref","c",[["D&C 38:41","dc-testament/dc/38.41"],"."]]]," unto all men."]],[3,["For we ourselves also were ",["sometimes",["study-note-ref","a",["GR once, formerly."]]]," foolish, ",["disobedient",["study-note-ref","b",[["TG Disobedience","tg/disobedience"],"."]]],", deceived, serving divers ",["lusts",["study-note-ref","c",[["TG Lust","tg/lust"],"."]]]," and pleasures, living in ",["malice",["study-note-ref","d",[["TG Malice","tg/malice"],"."]]]," and envy, hateful, ",["and",["clarity-word"]]," hating one another."]],[4,["But after that the kindness and love of God our Saviour toward man appeared,"]],[5,["Not by works of ",["righteousness",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Righteousness","tg/righteousness"],"."]]]," which we have done, but according to his ",["mercy",["study-note-ref","b",[["TG God, Mercy of","tg/god-mercy-of"],"."]]]," he saved us, by the ",["washing",["study-note-ref","c",[["TG Baptism, Essential","tg/baptism-essential"],"."]]]," of regeneration, and ",["renewing",["study-note-ref","d",[["TG Holy Ghost, Gifts of","tg/holy-ghost-gifts-of"],"."]]]," of the Holy Ghost;"]],[6,["Which he shed on us abundantly through Jesus Christ our Saviour;"]],[7,["That being ",["justified",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Justification","tg/justification"],"."]]]," by his grace, we should be made ",["heirs",["study-note-ref","b",[["D&C 70:8","dc-testament/dc/70.8"],"."]]]," according to the hope of eternal life."]],[8,[["This is",["clarity-word"]]," a faithful saying, and these things I will that thou affirm constantly, that they which have believed in God might be careful to maintain good ",["works",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Good Works","tg/good-works"],"."]]],". These things are good and profitable unto men."]],[9,["But avoid ",["foolish",["study-note-ref","a",[["2 Tim. 2:23 (23–26)","nt/2-tim/2.23"],"."]]]," questions, and genealogies, and ",["contentions",["study-note-ref","b",[["TG Contention","tg/contention"],"."]]],", and strivings about the law; for they are unprofitable and vain."]],[10,["A man that is an ",["heretick",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Apostasy of Individuals","tg/apostasy-of-individuals"],"."]]]," after the first and second ",["admonition",["study-note-ref","b",[["Matt. 18:17","nt/matt/18.17"],"."]]]," reject;"]],[11,["Knowing that he that is such is ",["subverted",["study-note-ref","a",["GR perverted, changed."]]],", and sinneth, being condemned of himself."]],[12,["When I shall send Artemas unto thee, or Tychicus, be diligent to come unto me to Nicopolis: for I have determined there to winter."]],[13,["Bring Zenas the lawyer and Apollos on their journey diligently, that nothing be wanting unto them."]],[14,["And let ",["ours",["study-note-ref","a",["GR our people."]]]," also learn to maintain ",["good works",["study-note-ref","b",[["Rom. 15:28 (25–28)","nt/rom/15.28"],"; ",["Philip. 4:17","nt/philip/4.17"],"."]]]," for necessary uses, that they be not unfruitful."]],[15,["All that are with me salute thee. Greet them that love us in the faith. Grace ",["be",["clarity-word"]]," with you all. Amen."]]],"volume":"nt"}